    <summary>07/00/1993: Masked Irish Republican Army (IRA) men seized control of a house and then kept watch over a Catholic prayer session as the perpetrators tried to bomb the Stormont Hotel in Belfast. Nineteen people attending the meeting were held hostage in the home of Danny McCaffrey, 52, whose car was used to transport the 500lb bomb across the city. Army explosives experts called to the Stormont Hotel defused the bomb.</summary>
